{
  "stem": "24137.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When they got better, relatives from the United States adopted them and didn't tell them that they were not their children.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the little girl, she knew, because she was-- she was, I think, seven.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she knew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The little boy didn't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And not the little boy and not the little girl were ever allowed to speak to me by these adopted relatives.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They denied the whole story, as though it never happened.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- on the day of the boy's bar mitzvah, way before, I called these little children-- I mean, they weren't little any more.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When we got big, already, in our 20s, I called [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and I asked to speak to them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Actually, no, it wasn't in our 20s.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was in our teen years.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I asked to speak to them, and their-- their relatives that adopted them said, I'm asking you, please do us a favor, and don't call us.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We want them to forget about it, and we don't want them to know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I said, can you ask them to speak to me and could-- could they tell me that?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they said, no, we don't-- we don't want them to even think about it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then when the boy had a bar mitzvah, his-- he came to a bar mitzvah age, when he was 13, this family went with him to the rabbi to learn, for-- prepare for the bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the rabbi said that this boy, once he's bar mitzvah, he should say Kaddish for his parents, because his parents deserve that their son should say Kaddish for them.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so they told the boy, and the boy had a nervous breakdown.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And for years, he was under psychiatrist care.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now he's fine.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
